Description







Scenario:

SecureDocs Inc., a leading financial services company, handles sensitive documents that only authorized employees can access. To ensure security, SecureDocs Inc. has implemented a Document Access System that verifies employee credentials before allowing access to confidential documents. The system uses a Proxy Pattern to authenticate employees and grant or deny access.

You are tasked with building this Document Access System using the Proxy Pattern, with properties instead of attributes.

 

Functionality:

In public class Employee, implement the following public field:

Datatype

Field Name

string

documentId

string

employeeName

Create a public constructor in class Employee with string documentId and string employeeName as arguments to set the values of documentId and employeeName.

 

Implement the following public method in public class AuthenticationRepo,

Method Name

Method Description

public List<Employee> GetAuthorizedEmployees()

This method returns a list of employees who are authorized to access documents.

Create a few authenticated employees using the following,

Document Id: D100; Employee Name: Alice

Document Id: D101; Employee Name: Bob

Document Id: D102; Employee Name: Charlie

 

Declare the following public method in public interface IDocumentAccess,

Method Name

Method Description

public string GetDocumentAccess(string documentId, string name)

This method handles the process of granting or denying access to documents.

 

Implement the following public method in public class DocumentService which implements the interface IDocumentAccess,

Method Name

Method Description

public string GetDocumentAccess(string documentId, string name)

This method returns a message indicating access is allowed for authorized employees by returning the string "<name> allowed to access the document".

Input and Output are case-sensitive.

 

Implement the following public method in public class ProxyService which implements the interface IDocumentAccess,

Method Name

Method Description

public string GetDocumentAccess(string documentId, string name)

This method checks if the employee is authorized to access the document.

It iterates through the list of authorized employees from AuthenticationRepo and compares the documentId and name with the provided parameters. If a match is found, it invokes the GetDocumentAccess method of DocumentService to grant access. If no match is found, it returns "Unauthorized".

Input and Output are case-sensitive.

 

In the Program class, implement the below-given Method.

Method:

public static void Main(string[] args)

Description:

-       Gather input from the user for the employee's name and document ID.

-       Call the GetDocumentAccess method of the ProxyService class to check if the employee is authorized to access the document.

-       Print the result, either granting access or returning "Unauthorized".

Input and Output are case-sensitive.

Refer to Sample input and output.

 

Note:

- Keep all methods public.

- Inputs should only be gathered in the Main method.

- Do not use Environment.Exit() to terminate the program. 

- Do not change the given code template.

- In the Sample Input / Output provided, the highlighted text in bold corresponds to the input given by the user and the rest of the text represents the output.

 

Sample Input 1:

Enter the Employee name:

Alice

Enter the Document Id:

D100

Sample Output 1:

Alice allowed to access the document.

 

Sample Input 2:

Enter the Employee name:

John

Enter the Document Id:

D111

Sample Output 2:

Unauthorized

